#  Pokepedia - Interactive Pokemon Explorer

A modern web application for browsing and exploring Pokemon using the PokeAPI. 

# Features

## Main Pokemon List
-*Browse 200 Pokemon* - View the first 200 Pokemon from Generation I-II
-*Type Filtering* - Filter Pokemon by 18 different types with color-coded buttons
-*Smart Search* - Search by Pokemon name or number
-*Dual Search Modes* - Toggle between searching by number or name
-*Show All Option* - Quick reset to view all Pokemon

## Pokemon Details Page
-*Pokemon Image* - Animation
-*Type Badges* - Color-coded type indicators
-*Quick Stats* - View weight, height, and signature moves
-*Pokemon Description* - Text from the Pokedex
-*Navigation* - Easy previous and next Pokemon navigation 

## Design Features
-*Dark Theme* - Dark gray (#292929) background
-*Orbitron Font* - Gaming inspired typography
-*Smooth Animations* - Hover effects, floating images, glowing search bar
-*Fully Responsive* - Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile

# Technologies Used

-*HTML5* - Semantic markup
-*CSS3* - Custom styling with animations and responsive design
-*Vanilla JavaScript* - No frameworks, pure ES6+
-*PokeAPI* - RESTful Pokemon data API

# Project Structure

```
PokemonProject/
├─ pokemon.html              - Main Pokemon list page
├─ detail.html              - Pokemon detail page
├─ style.css                - Main stylesheet
├─ pokemon.js               - Main page JavaScript
├─ pokemon-detail.js        - Detail page JavaScript
└─ images/                  - UI icons and assets
    ├─ pokeball.svg
    ├─ search.svg
    ├─ sorting.svg
    ├─ cross.svg
    ├─ back-to-home.svg
    ├─ chevron_left.svg
    ├─ chevron_right.svg
    ├─ weight.svg
    └─ height.svg
```
##  API Integration

This project uses the [PokeAPI](https://pokeapi.co/) for all Pokemon data:

*Endpoints Used:**
-`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon?limit=200` - List of 200 Pokemon
-`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/{id}` - Individual Pokemon data
-`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon-species/{id}` - Pokemon descriptions
-`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/type/{type}` - Pokemon by type

*Data Retrieved:*
- Pokemon sprites (Dream World, Official Artwork)
- Stats (weight, height, moves)
- Types and type colors
- Pokedex flavor text
- Pokemon abilities and characteristics


